The paper deals with the optimization of wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networks and communications (cs.NI). The paper also involves the use of mathematical models and optimization techniques, which are relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the business models for multi-operator cooperation, which is related to social and information networks (cs.SI) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
